The paper proposes a new paradigm for telecommunications using concepts from complex system science, specifically agent-based modeling and graph theoretical abstractions. The focus is on understanding and analyzing network complexity in the context of 5G networks and IoT. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Multiagent Systems (cs.MA), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Information Theory (cs.IT).
